commitResults.messageBody:
This is to check if the command contains a delete, which will initiate the logic for delete tasks.

Ui class: Add delete Ui

TaskList class: Add delete method

Supporting methods using Java Collections for deleting task in TaskList.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add folder for enums Add CommandName.java class in folder enums
commitResults.messageBody:
Using enums for command names, we can implement a cleaner way to store and identify the different
command names. We will implement the logic by refactoring the Parser.java class.

Parser class: Refactored code, deleted boolean methods such as isDelete(), and used switch statements

Code simplicity and avoid duplication of code by using switch statements.
This allows for easier scalability and maintenance of code logic.

ToDo, DeadLine, and Event switch statements have fallthrough to prevent code duplication.

Storage class will contain the logic for writing the file into the user device and will
also load existing user data.

Add toFileFormat() to task, event, deadLine and toDo classes to allow code to write
in a specific format to save into the device.

We will save the file in the Jar class once user inputs "bye".
